        "description": "Testing in a Docker environment with a single Kafka instance using a single Zookeeper instance. Restarting the Zookeeper container will cause it to receive a new IP address. Kafka will never be able to reconnect to Zookeeper and will hang indefinitely. Updating DNS or /etc/hosts with the new IP address will not help the client to reconnect as the zookeeper/client/StaticHostProvider resolves the connection string hosts at creation time and never re-resolves.\r\n\r\nA solution would be for the client to notice that connection attempts fail and attempt to re-resolve the hostnames in the connectString.",
        "duedate": null,
        "environment": "Ubuntu 14.04 host, Docker containers for Zookeeper & Kafka",
